"title": "5168: muteness",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5168: muteness",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The inability to speak or to make sounds comprehensible as speech.</p>\n<h2>Physical muteness</h2>\n<h3>A disability, sometimes associated with demon-possession, healed by Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:32-Matt9:33\">MAT 9:32–9:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:22\">MAT 12:22</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:14\">LUK 11:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:30-Matt15:31\">MAT 15:30–15:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:31-Mark7:37\">MRK 7:31–7:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:14-Mark9:29\">MRK 9:14–9:29</a></p>\n<h3>Healing as a Messianic sign</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:22-Matt12:23\">MAT 12:22–12:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa32:4\">ISA 32:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa35:6\">ISA 35:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:23\">MAT 4:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:33\">MAT 9:33</a></p>\n<h2>God and muteness</h2>\n<h3>God gives and withholds speech</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:11-Exod4:12\">EXO 4:11–4:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:10\">EXO 4:10</a></p>\n<h3>God may impose muteness in judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:20\">LUK 1:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:64\">LUK 1:64</a></p>\n<h3>God may silence his prophets</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek3:26\">EZK 3:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek24:27\">EZK 24:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek33:22\">EZK 33:22</a></p>\n<h2>The muteness of idols</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:2\">1CO 12:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:26\">1KI 18:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps115:5\">PSA 115:5</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps135:16\">PSA 135:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:26\">ISA 41:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:28\">ISA 41:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa46:7\">ISA 46:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:5\">JER 10:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab2:18-Hab2:19\">HAB 2:18–2:19</a></p>\n<h2>Spiritual aspects of muteness and silence</h2>\n<h3>Evil silenced by God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job5:16\">JOB 5:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps63:11\">PSA 63:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:42\">PSA 107:42</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:63\">EZK 16:63</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:4\">MRK 3:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:19\">ROM 3:19</a></p>\n<h3>Evil silenced by godliness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:15\">1PE 2:15</a></p>\n<h3>Silence on earth</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab2:20\">HAB 2:20</a></p>\n<h3>Silence in heaven</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev8:1\">REV 8:1</a></p>\n<h3>God opens believers' mouths in praise</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:3\">PSA 40:3</a></p>\n<h2>Voluntary muteness</h2>\n<h3>Of David</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps38:13-Ps38:14\">PSA 38:13–38:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps39:1-Ps39:3\">PSA 39:1–39:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps39:9\">PSA 39:9</a></p>\n<h3>Of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:7\">ISA 53:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:32\">ACT 8:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps38:13\">PSA 38:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:62-Matt26:63\">MAT 26:62–26:63</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:60-Mark14:61\">MRK 14:60–14:61</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:12-Matt27:14\">MAT 27:12–27:14</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:5\">MRK 15:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:9\">JHN 19:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:8-Luke23:9\">LUK 23:8–23:9</a></p>",
